62
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,070
You are...

63
00:03:55,530 --> 00:03:56,650
Young Master?

64
00:03:58,670 --> 00:03:59,460
I am

65
00:03:59,890 --> 00:04:01,460
Manyi's childhood friend.

66
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,920
I'm her best friend.

67
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:04,540
My name is Cui Jun.

68
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:08,990
Her childhood friend?

69
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:12,990
Is he here to ruin the relationship of my brother and Manyi

70
00:04:12,990 --> 00:04:14,650
in the name of her good friend?

71
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:16,700
What are you murmuring?

72
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:18,430
Let me in.

73
00:04:18,450 --> 00:04:20,910
Wait, my brother and Manyi

74
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:23,080
went out today.

75
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:26,290
They haven't come back yet. Come another day.

76
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:29,030
It's alright. I'll wait for her inside.

77
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,210
No, no.

78
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:33,870
Since you are an old friend of Manyi,

79
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:36,630
I'll be honest with you.

80
00:04:37,030 --> 00:04:38,950
Manyi is in trouble.

81
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:40,400
What?

82
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,960
Let's talk on the way.

83
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:42,700
Let's go.

84
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:47,930
[Wen's Mansion]

85
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:45,870
What happened

86
00:04:46,470 --> 00:04:47,510
to her?

87
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:01,220
Have a look at straw hats!

88
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,090
Is she the one who always targets Manyi?

89
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:07,410
Yes, our mission today is to follow her.

90
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,770
We must find the location of the qin playing meeting.

91
00:05:09,770 --> 00:05:10,590
Can you do that?

92
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:12,440
Why can't I? Let's go.

93
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:16,570
Come and take a look. High-quality peanuts.

94
00:05:24,380 --> 00:05:26,430
Mr. Jun, when will you

95
00:05:26,710 --> 00:05:29,110
tell your parents about our relationship?

96
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:20,310
My lady, it seems that they are not stalking.

97
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:22,610
They are just lovers on a date.

98
00:06:22,930 --> 00:06:25,650
How shameless in public!

99
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,990
We lost her.

100
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:36,770
Don't worry.

101
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:39,230
I've never lost anyone.

102
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:49,810
I found her.

103
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:50,950
I knew it.

104
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,159
No one

105
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:54,360
can escape from me.

106
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:02,860
Where did she go?

107
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:08,120
[Enjoying Qin Pavilion]

108
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:21,070
That Old Crow.

109
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:22,600
I played the qin tirelessly,

110
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,300
while you are carefree.

111
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,570
If I don't give you a slingshot,

112
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,240
I can't get rid of my hatred.

113
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:35,070
It's you.

114
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:40,080
What a coincidence.

115
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,190
Yes, sure.

116
00:07:41,990 --> 00:07:44,730
I'm here for this fake mountain.

117
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,240
What about you?

118
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:48,560
I am trying my new slingshot

119
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:50,120
to see if I can hit that bird.

120
00:07:51,150 --> 00:07:52,159
Yes.

121
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:54,270
Please.

122
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:54,860
Go ahead.

123
00:07:54,860 --> 00:07:55,990
Go ahead.

124
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:57,790
Go ahead.

125
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:03,110
How dare this Old Crow tease me!

126
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,150
He wants to report to my father

127
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:06,190
that I squander money

128
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:07,470
and will even reduce my pocket money.

129
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:09,030
I'll chop his legs and then you shoot his head.

130
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:10,130
That's exactly what I want. Beat him!

131
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:10,670
Beat him!

132
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:16,420
No, Mr. Wen is here. If he sees what you do,

133
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:18,020
he'll definitely make you suffer.

134
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:20,010
I'm afraid too. I might hurt innocent people

135
00:08:20,010 --> 00:08:21,560
if I can't aim at him precisely.

136
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,660
What should we do?

137
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,820
I have a perfect idea.

138
00:08:27,710 --> 00:08:28,390
What?

139
00:08:28,790 --> 00:08:30,160
Let's wear masks.

140
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:31,840
When the Old Crow is alone,

141
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:34,770
beat him unconscious, tie him up and throw him to the wilderness.

142
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:36,039
If he can't come back tomorrow,

143
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,659
he won't be able to attend the qin playing meeting

144
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,659
and won't be able to report to your father.

145
00:08:39,659 --> 00:08:42,250
Our crisis will naturally be solved.

146
00:08:56,430 --> 00:08:57,620
It's delicious.

147
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:00,670
Can I have another bowl?

148
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:03,540
Manyi, why do you have such an appetite today?

149
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:05,670
Are you pregnant?

150
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,060
No, no. Absolutely not.

151
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,680
It's just I've made a perfect plan.

152
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:13,310
Wait for the show tomorrow.

153
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,650
Lord Du was attacked by two thieves today.

154
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:21,540
Those who report the clues will be rewarded.

155
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:23,590
[Wen's Mansion]

156
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,610
Lord Du was attacked by two thieves today.

157
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,590
Those who report the clues will be rewarded.

158
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,890
How could he come back so soon?

159
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:37,050
I will be doomed if they find I am the one who attacked him.

160
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:38,920
I will also be doomed if I am exposed on the stage.

161
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,880
I will be doomed anyway.

162
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:43,810
Why are you still in the mood to play the qin?

163
00:09:43,810 --> 00:09:45,500
I will be doomed.

164
00:09:46,370 --> 00:09:47,070
No.

165
00:09:47,530 --> 00:09:48,390
You have to run.

166
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,280
It's better for me to hide for the time being.

167
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,280
Instead of escaping,

168
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:56,380
it's better for you to face the challenge head-on.

169
00:09:56,380 --> 00:09:58,180
That's easy for you to say.

170
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:00,360
Think about a solution for me.

171
00:10:02,190 --> 00:10:03,590
Are you not running away?

172
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:05,920
Do you want to practicing the qin?

173
00:10:06,770 --> 00:10:08,790
Tell me your ideas.

174
00:10:09,180 --> 00:10:11,410
Play the qin as usual tomorrow.

175
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:15,200
But when you play it, you need to pretend that it doesn't fit

176
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:19,090
and break the strings with your strength.

177
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,940
Then you can pretend that your fingers are injured

178
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:24,760
and can't play the qin. This will be a way out.

179
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,560
That sounds practical. If the strings are broken

180
00:10:27,590 --> 00:10:29,970
and my fingers are injured, how can I play the qin?

181
00:10:29,970 --> 00:10:30,550
Let's go.

182
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:34,570
I was so scared that I didn't eat enough. I'll get some snacks.

183
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:45,260
[A Talented Girl Grows Up]

184
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,970
No, it's not true.

185
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:10,980
My fingers are bleeding.

186
00:11:11,190 --> 00:11:12,070
Cheng Manyi!

187
00:11:12,070 --> 00:11:15,430
I can't play the song I love anymore.

188
00:11:15,430 --> 00:11:18,390
I'm useless.

189
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,320
Honey.

190
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,460
Does it still hurt?

191
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:30,900
No.

192
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:33,480
It doesn't hurt anymore.

193
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:48,240
Is she having a sweet dream again?

194
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:30,550
Your Highness.

195
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:35,080
I got a jade pendant yesterday

196
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,980
which looks exactly the same

197
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:38,710
as yours.

198
00:12:38,710 --> 00:12:41,350
So I brought it to show you.

199
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,870
Yes, it's mine.

200
00:12:46,050 --> 00:12:47,930
I lost it a few days ago.

201
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,820
Fortunately, it was found by you.

202
00:12:50,490 --> 00:12:51,370
It was lost?

203
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,520
Did you lose it on the saddle?

204
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:59,630
You're so heavy. Come on!

205
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,120
What saddle?

206
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,150
I have never seen any saddle.

207
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,440
Don't make assumptions

208
00:13:07,780 --> 00:13:09,450
if you have no evidence.

209
00:13:11,210 --> 00:13:15,250
I will report what happened yesterday to His Majesty

210
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:17,400
and ask His Majesty to make a decision.

211
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,050
Your Highness.

212
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:22,150
The qin playing meeting is about to begin.

213
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:23,030
Please.

214
00:13:28,940 --> 00:13:32,790
[Enjoying Qin Pavilion]

215
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,520
It is about to begin.

216
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,030
We're waiting.

217
00:13:36,060 --> 00:13:37,100
Come here.

218
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,210
Take a good seat.

219
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,170
Are you nervous?

220
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:42,190
I am excited.

221
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:44,450
I am too excited to wait any longer.

222
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:50,710
Mr. Zhang, come here.

223
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:00,280
Everyone, it's an honor

224
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:04,550
have you, talented scholars and intellectuals, here today.

225
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:08,310
This meeting is honored by your presence.

226
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:12,840
The qin playing meeting starts now.

227
00:14:13,030 --> 00:14:17,500
Let's welcome Cheng Manyi, the World's Greatest Talented Woman.

228
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,940
She'll play the qin now.

229
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:22,360
Bravo! Bravo!

230
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:23,590
Young Madam, come on!

231
00:14:25,590 --> 00:14:27,670
Please bring the qin here.

232
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,260
What are they doing?

233
00:14:38,260 --> 00:14:40,110
I'm afraid an ordinary qin is not good enough for you to play.

234
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:41,670
It might affect your performance.

235
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:44,940
That's why I asked people to look for these qin with high quality.

236
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:48,170
They all have beautiful sounds. Feel free to choose.

237
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:54,430
Vice Censor-in-Chief Du, you're really considerate.

238
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:57,490
There's more.

239
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:58,870
Guards!

240
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:04,570
Who is he?

241
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:08,170
I'm afraid someone might get hurt or feel uncomfortable while playing the qin.

242
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:10,050
So I asked a famous doctor

243
00:15:10,070 --> 00:15:12,400
to prepare the medicine and provide first aid here.

244
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,200
Please play the qin.

245
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:17,470
Miss Cheng, please.

246
00:15:23,710 --> 00:15:27,230
Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

247
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,090
Guards, put down the curtains around.

248
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:48,890
Mr. Wen, why?

249
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:53,070
Vice Censor-in-Chief Du, let me explain it to you. My wife is introverted.

250
00:15:53,070 --> 00:15:55,860
She is surrounded by many talented people here.

251
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:57,920
I'm afraid she might feel uncomfortable.

252
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,680
If the gauze can be put down,

253
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:02,110
she will have no worry to play the qin here.

254
00:16:02,130 --> 00:16:03,580
We will wait for her outside.

255
00:16:03,580 --> 00:16:07,240
It's like seeing the moon in the water and enjoying the flowers amid the mist.

256
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:08,510
Isn't it wonderful?

257
00:16:39,090 --> 00:16:41,950
What Miss Cheng is playing is a traditional yet beautiful song.

258
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:45,370
It sounds as beautiful as shattering jade and dew-weeping lotuses.

259
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:46,170
That's right.

260
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:52,430
Impossible. She can't play the qin.

261
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:54,600
There must be something wrong inside.

262
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:56,210
Why can't it be possible?

263
00:16:56,710 --> 00:16:57,700
I'll take a look.

264
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:02,430
Will there be anything wrong?

265
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:05,520
Let's see who's playing the qin.

266
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:10,270
Gosh, you scared me.

267
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:13,760
Sorry.

268
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:25,540
Brother, look.

269
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,819
This is the map of the Enjoying Qin Pavilion that Cui Jun and I drew

270
00:17:27,819 --> 00:17:30,110
according to the proportion.

271
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:35,700
That's great. It is like a fortress.

272
00:17:32,870 --> 00:17:37,300
[Shaped like a fortress]

273
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:39,310
Someone can hide in the center

274
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:41,720
to play a two-man act.

275
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:45,850
I see. You know that it is impossible for Manyi

276
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:48,210
to be an excellent qin player

277
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:49,250
in a short period of time.

